cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.HC 

This paper is about using machine learning to provide explanations for predictions, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of embeddings and multi-task learning, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions natural language processing (NLP) and the use of textual explanations, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The two domains used for empirical evaluation, chemical odor and skin cancer prediction, fall under computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC), respectively.
